refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.notes;
&function.mysql_change_user; will always cause the current database connection to behave as if was a completely new database connection, regardless of if the operation was completed successfully. This reset includes performing a rollback on any active transactions, closing all temporary tables, and unlocking all locked tables.
If desired, the NULL value may be passed resulting in only changing the user and not selecting a database.
